text.tspan: Let's say we have a libary for video decoding and we have to decide what license to give it.
So as the developer/publisher of the libary we have to do the choice what we want:
Don't we care who can use our libary and want others to adapt to our choice.
Do we want as many as possible free projects to use our libary but we want to prevent unfree projects to use it
we should multi-license with copyleft (but we force projects without copyleft to use ours license).
Do we want as many projects as possible to be able to use our libary and don't want to restrict them and we don't care about
commercial use we could use a license without copyleft (Apple uses a lot of those).
